# Garam, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Garam () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Yeravninsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 208 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Garam is located near the Bolshoy Yeravna lake, part of the Yeravna-Khorga Lake System. 10&nbsp;km northwest of Sosnovo-Ozerskoye, the nearest rural locality.
